page.title: 03THE GREAT STOUR
page.content: It goes from Wye to Ashford.In the river stour there is pike and trout.There is two fields both sides of it.They are rough grazing and a wheat field.There is some lilypads and weed in it.The weed looks like grass. The creatures are cadis fly larvaes and its eggs.There are leeches in the weed.On one side of the river it goes fast on the other it is slow. At the sides there are some Alder trees. Near Wye there are some sewage works on the river stour. The river Stour has many small streams running into it. The brook from our village of Brook runs into it.
